radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is fluid filled and appears markedly dilated, measuring 13 mm in diameter near the tip. Included views of the lung bases are clear. The liver, gallbladder, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, stomach, and intra-abdominal loops of small bowel are normal. No free fluid or free air. Very trace stranding adjacent to the tip of the appendix is present. No acute fracture or dislocation.
